From 9d465a5ed655a32accda7ccd92f7d9b26fca6c62 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:31:02 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase D polish: move editor pane top padding so sticky
 headers anchor flush

Reported: sticky diff card headers stuck to the top of
`.krt-pr-editor` but the editor's `padding-top: 24px` left an
empty gap above the header (the padding region shows the editor
background between the editor's top edge and the sticky header).

CSS sticky `top: 0` anchors at the scroll container's
**padding-box** top edge, which is the inside of the border. With
a non-zero `padding-top` on the scroll container, that edge is
above where non-sticky content normally lives, so the sticky
header floats inside the padding region with empty space below it
(or above, depending on perspective) before the rest of the
content reaches it.

Move the 24px top padding off the scroll container and onto the
PR header (`.krt-pr-editor-header { padding-top: 24px }`) so the
visual breathing room above the PR header is preserved while
sticky children anchor flush with the editor's top edge. Side
padding stays on the scroll container; bottom padding too (it
doesn't affect sticky).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css   | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
index d7059967206..2af0801889f 100644
--- a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
@@ -7,7 +7,10 @@
 	display: flex;
 	flex-direction: column;
 	box-sizing: border-box;
-	padding: 24px 32px 48px;
+	/* Top padding moved to `.krt-pr-editor-header` so sticky children
+	 * (diff card headers, etc.) anchor at `top: 0` of the visible
+	 * scrollport without leaving an empty padding gap above them. */
+	padding: 0 32px 48px;
 	gap: 18px;
 	overflow: auto;
 	font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
@@ -18,6 +21,9 @@
 	align-items: flex-start;
 	justify-content: space-between;
 	gap: 16px;
+	/* Visual breathing room that used to live on the scroll
+	 * container's `padding-top`. See `.krt-pr-editor`. */
+	padding-top: 24px;
 }
 
 .krt-pr-editor-header-text {
